The subject analyzes the functional-semantic fields of the Russian language, the functional peculiarities of the grammatical categories of the language. The course presupposes previous knowledge of formal grammar.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide an overview of the functional-semantic fields of the Russian language. By offering students practical tasks, to develop their skills to analyze Russian-language grammatical categories, syntactical constructions and other language means in the text from the standpoint of functional-semantic fields.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of the subject a student: 1) knows the basics of functional grammar and critically evaluates different approaches to the functional descriptions of a language; 2) analyzes grammatical forms, the syntactical constructions of speech and other language means from the standpoint of functional-semantic fields; 3) emphasizes the functional approach when teaching grammar to foreign students.
